Smartphone-Streaming-Portable%2Fdp%2FB0CCBX7RP7&amp;uuid=RO7bUzAh02zlvkFw2962">亚马逊</a>预订。</p><h2>银河手表 6 </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f37fad90-2bb5-11ee-bfe2-a02434649ba1" style="height:1050px;width:1750px;" alt="三星 Galaxy Watch 6 和 Galaxy Watch 6 经典" data-uuid="42516696-c11d-31e3-bfff-5a39c7be7786"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>夏季 Unpacked 最大的更新可以说是针对三星最小的计算设备。该公司推出了 Galaxy Watch 6 系列，对 Wear OS 手表进行了一些<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-6-hands-on-the-spinning-bezels-triumphant-return-110047694.html">人们迫切要求的改进</a>。最值得注意的是，旋转表圈又回来了——购买 Galaxy Watch 6 Classic，您就可以通过触觉滚动浏览应用程序和小部件。这两款手表都提供更大、更亮的显示屏、升级的处理器、更大的电池和“一键式”表带更换系统。</p><p> Galaxy Watch 6 系列将于 8 月 11 日上市。您可以通过<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvd2F0Y2hlcy9nYWxheHktd2F0Y2g2L2J1eS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU0MzU3NjA1LTkzNmUtNDZkZC04MzMyLTEzMWFjYTE0NzUwNCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAfEd9Riiq31xUCzVoTbONi9BUEJprq2DXP9spuuBsO97&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Fwatches%2Fgalaxy-watch6%2Fbuy%2F&amp;uuid=DGTBKsb15y1VfiWD0083">三星</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWkYdmmLB7dgUhny4NIQ-npynMzV7rOY9GCLPI_w0YtX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Bluetooth-Smartwatch-Personalized-Advanced%2Fdp%2FB0CCQR2LM6&amp;uuid=jrhyVzk2I7Afrgy61083">亚马逊</a>进行预订，基本型号起价为 300 美元，经典型号起价为 400 美元。</p><h2> Galaxy Tab S9 </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/671fa240-2bb7-11ee-aff7-3238dff675dd" style="height:1280px;width:1920px;" alt="三星 Galaxy Tab S9 Ultra" data-uuid="66805a15-6da7-3fa3-a4cb-7f8b5110dd18"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Mat Smith/Engadget</div></figure><p>三星通过推出 Galaxy Tab S9 系列来迎合高端 Android 平板电脑的粉丝。虽然设计没有太大变化（主要是更窄的边框），但它仍然是一个<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-tab-s9-ultra-hands-on-a-premium-tablet-with-water-protection-110020872.html">重大升级</a>，包括动态刷新率 AMOLED 屏幕、定制的 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 芯片、更强大的扬声器，甚至平板电脑和随附的 IP68 防水防尘性能S笔。</p><p>该系列将于 8 月 11 日发售，并在<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvdGFibGV0cy9nYWxheHktdGFiLXM5L2J1eS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjZiMDVhMmNlLWJjZWUtNGYyZC1iNjM4LTM5Yjc5NjdhNWMyNSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZ4tEBc82lsOEtnVOLi-xwqebtArSLeAFZ2ZUOMvBSon&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftablets%2Fgalaxy-tab-s9%2Fbuy%2F&amp;uuid=3JyvnjZUnwBlUaCg0432">三星</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TQU1TVU5HLUdhbGF4eS0xMS1JbmNoLTEyOEdCLUJlaWdlL2RwL0IwQzRCQ05SVlE_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMXJkLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI2YjA1YTJjZS1iY2VlLTRmMmQtYjYzOC0zOWI3OTY3YTVjMjUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAaJ21uRpqZy1ZkRxS262DrykXkb3t_Nz7hIgdZ5RIV38&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Galaxy-11-Inch-128GB-Beige%2Fdp%2FB0C4BCNRVQ&amp;uuid=Vx0aCEXdNY9WGQP11432">亚马逊</a>开放预订。 11 英寸 Galaxy Tab S9 起价为 800 美元，而 12.4 英寸 Tab S9+ 起价为 1,000 美元。巨大的 14.6 英寸 Tab S9 Ultra 售价至少 1,200 美元。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/summer-samsung-unpacked-2023-everything-announced-at-the-event-134721886.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/summer-samsung-unpacked-2023-everything-announced-at-the-event-134721886.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 10cea5dd-7703-403b-a411-9f089ec5c3d5</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 26 Jul 2023 13:47:21 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690379998</ingested><modified> 2023-07-26T14:00:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/cb2aada0-2bb9-11ee-bfbf-ebc3bbb79401" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/cb2aada0-2bb9-11ee-bfbf-ebc3bbb79401" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[How to choose the best TV for gaming right now]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>过去，为 PlayStation 或 Xbox 寻找合适的电视需要仔细查看规格表。然而，如今，最适合游戏的电视通常是您能买到的最好的电视。虽然没有人<em>需要</em>在客厅里放置一台精美的电视来享受精彩的视频游戏，但正确的电视机可以帮助您最大限度地提高游戏体验。如果您不确定从哪里开始，我们在下面列出了一些购买合适型号的有用建议，以及您今天可以购买的最佳游戏电视的一些首选。</p><h2>在游戏电视中寻找什么</h2><p>无论您是否用它来玩游戏，所有好的电视都建立在相同的基础上。您需要 4K 分辨率（这是当今的标准）、足够的亮度、高对比度、深沉且均匀的黑色色调、在准确度和饱和度之间找到适当平衡的色彩以及宽视角。特别是对于视频游戏，您需要一台具有最小输入延迟和快速运动响应的电视，并且在快速移动的物体后面没有模糊或其他不需要的伪像。当然，找到一套既符合所有这些条件又符合您的预算的套装可能很棘手。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>目前，顶级 OLED 电视将为游戏或其他活动提供最佳的图像质量。然而，好的 OLED 电视的成本仍然高于 LED LCD 替代品，而且对于那些在光线特别充足的环境中使用电视机的人来说，有些电视的亮度可能不够。如果您选择液晶电视，带有微型 LED 的先进背光和有效的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.howtogeek.com/742183/what-is-full-array-local-dimming/">全阵列局部调光</a>通常会改善对比度和照明细节，而量子点滤光片可以增强色彩。</p><p>您无需担心的一件事是 8K 支持。尽管 PS5 和 Xbox Series X 在技术上能够输出 8K 视频，但很少有游戏是针对该分辨率制作的，而且 8K 的实际好处<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv/reviews/by-size/size-to-distance-relationship">极其微乎其微</a>，除非你打算坐在离大电视太近的地方。市场上为数不多的8K电视也<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-2023-8k-mini-led-tv-starts-at-5000-163559445.html">非常昂贵</a>。</p><p>尽管如此，在为新游戏机或高端显卡购买电视时，您应该特别注意一些术语。</p><h3> HDMI 2.1</h3><p>为了充分利用 PlayStation 5 或 Xbox Series X/S，您的电视应完全支持 HDMI 2.1。这是 HDMI 规范的最新重大更新，实现了更高的最大带宽（从 HDMI 2.0 的 18 Gbps 上升到每秒 48 GB），以及一些特别有利于游戏的功能。其中包括可变刷新率 (VRR) 和自动低延迟模式 (ALLM)，我们将在下面进一步详细介绍。</p><p>除此之外，HDMI 2.1 的主要优点也许是它能够在 PS5 和 Xbox Series X 等现代游戏机上以高达 120Hz 的刷新率传输超清晰的 4K 视频，或者在功能强大的游戏 PC 上以高达 144Hz 的刷新率传输超清晰的 4K 视频。并非所有<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.psu.com/news/all-ps5-games-that-support-120-fps-the-smoothest-games-on-playstation-5/">PS5</a>或<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.techradar.com/news/ps5-and-xbox-series-x-games-with-120fps-support">Xbox Series X/S</a>游戏都支持那么高的帧速率（有些游戏仅在较低分辨率下支持），但那些支持的游戏在运动时看起来和感觉起来会特别流畅。 HDMI 2.1 还支持<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/enhancedaudioreturnchannel">增强型音频回传通道</a>(eARC)，允许从连接到电视的源设备向兼容的条形音箱或接收器提供更高质量的 5.1 和 7.1 通道音频。</p><p>电视的 HDMI 2.1 端口越完整越好。 “完整”是那里的关键词。据<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://tftcentral.co.uk/articles/when-hdmi-2-1-isnt-hdmi-2-1"><em>TFT Central</em></a>报道，由于 HDMI 2.1 向后兼容 HDMI 2.0，因此电视和显示器制造商可以将 HDMI 端口标记为“HDMI 2.1”，即使他们缺乏对该规范升级功能的完整（或任何）支持。我们推荐以下几款具有真正 HDMI 2.1 端口的电视，但如果您购买新电视用于游戏，请确保您选择的电视机不会试图隐藏您可能认为必要的任何功能。</p><h3> HDR——高动态范围</h3><p>HDR 是指电视能够显示图片最暗部分和最亮部分之间更大范围的能力。这种更宽的范围可以显示标准动态范围 (SDR) 电视上可能缺失的细节，无论是在图像的极暗区域，尤其是在极亮区域。 HDR 通常还会改进色彩再现，显示更大的调色板，更鲜艳的色彩，使内容更接近其创作者的原始愿景。</p><p>要获得 HDR 图像，您需要掌握利用该技术的内容和能够显示该内容的电视。 HDR 也有多种格式，通常分为使用静态元数据的格式（例如 HDR10）和使用动态元数据的格式（例如 HDR10+、杜比视界）。简而言之，后者允许电视在每个场景甚至每帧的基础上优化其亮度和颜色，而前者对整个给定内容使用一组优化设置。对这些格式的支持可能会有所不同，具体取决于您使用的电视、内容和游戏机。例如，Xbox Series X 和 S 支持<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.dolby.com/experience/xbox/#gref">杜比视界游戏</a>，而 PS5 则不支持。</p><p>好消息是，您在 2023 年购买的大多数电视都以某种方式支持 HDR，即使是在预算端市场也是如此。问题是有些电视比其他电视更能充分利用 HDR。对于 HDR 中掌握的<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-11-26-disney-the-mandalorian-hdr-quality.html">实际内容</a>也是如此。特别是视频游戏，设计利用 HDR 的游戏并不像电影那样多（尽管数量在增长），而且<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-10-31-red-dead-redemption-2-not-true-hdr.html">质量差异</a><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cyberpunk-2077-patch-105-015615945.html">往往更大</a>。</p><h3> HGiG — HDR 游戏兴趣小组</h3><p>HGiG 代表<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.hgig.org/">HDR 游戏兴趣小组</a>。索尼和微软都是成员，许多电视制造商和游戏开发商也是成员。这意味着，理想情况下，所有组都会传达信息，以便您可以在控制台或 PC 上启动新游戏并让它自动识别您的显示器。一旦发生这种情况，游戏可以调整内部设置以适应显示器的功能，并为您提供尽可能最佳的图像质量，而不会丢失屏幕最亮或最暗区域的细节。例如，黑暗隧道尽头的日光可能会描绘出明亮的环境，而不是看起来像曝光过度的白色斑点。</p><p>这是一件好事，但现实有点复杂。并非所有电视都会在其设置菜单中突出显示 HGiG 兼容性，而只有部分 PlayStation 和 Xbox 游戏能够识别并遵循这些准则。 If an HGiG option is listed in your TV&#39;s tone mapping settings, you should turn it on prior to running the console&#39;s HDR settings. Then, if you&#39;re playing a game that supports HDR and HGiG, you should be in good shape without having to adjust the various luminance levels again. Still, how all of this looks to <em>you</em> might differ depending on your TV and the game you&#39;re playing. Owners of certain LG OLED models, for instance, may prefer their TV&#39;s Dynamic Tone Mapping setting. Use whatever settings you think look best.</p><h3> ALLM — Auto Low Latency Mode</h3><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/autolowlatencymode">ALLM</a> allows a source (like your PS5 or Xbox) to tell the display to switch into a mode that reduces lag between receiving each frame of an image and displaying it on the TV. This cuts out additional processing that could be the milliseconds of difference between landing a precise input or not. A good modern TV can automatically switch to game mode, then back out when you&#39;d rather watch a movie or TV show.</p><h3> VRR — Variable Refresh Rate</h3><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.hdmi.org/spec21sub/variablerefreshrate">VRR</a> is a familiar feature to PC gamers, but it&#39;s still relatively new for most TVs. Most players have experienced slowdown, screen tearing or stuttering as a system struggles to render each frame at the target speed, which is most commonly 30 or 60 fps on a TV. With VRR, everything stays in sync — your display won&#39;t show the next frame until it&#39;s ready, which can make things feel smoother and more responsive, even if the system fails to deliver on its target frame rate.</p><p> With VRR, however, everything stays in sync — your display won&#39;t show the next frame until it&#39;s ready, which can make things feel smoother and more responsive, even if the system fails to deliver on its target of 30, 60 or even 120 fps.</p><p> There are a few different implementations of VRR available, including <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:NVIDIA;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f52348f6-2304-415e-b16c-1fb252794066&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=NVIDIA&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmNTIzNDhmNi0yMzA0LTQxNWUtYjE2Yy0xZmIyNTI3OTQwNjYiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnZpZGlhLmNvbS9lbi11cy9nZWZvcmNlL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2ctc3luYy1tb25pdG9ycy8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImY1ODQzYTUwLTFjMTEtNDllZS1iZjg2LTJmYTVkNDIxOTQ0MCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAW-0GsAVE8eGkzSggX3VcDBHrBy1gmYQ4YocWtXb-8wc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-us%2Fgeforce%2Fproducts%2Fg-sync-monitors%2F">Nvidia&#39;s G-Sync,</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.amd.com/en/technologies/free-sync">AMD&#39;s FreeSync</a> and the HDMI Forum&#39;s VRR spec, which is part of the full HDMI 2.1 standard. Both a TV and an input device need to support the same VRR tech for it to work, and different devices may only support VRR within a specific refresh rate window. On a 120Hz display, for instance, the PS5&#39;s VRR only works between 48Hz and 120Hz.</p><p> As a reminder, the <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ps5-variable-refresh-rate-vrr-release-date-193228613.html">PS5 supports</a> HDMI Forum VRR, the Xbox Series X/S support HDMI Forum VRR and FreeSync, while gaming PCs may support G-Sync or FreeSync depending on whether they use a Nvidia or AMD graphics card. A great gaming TV supports all the big VRR formats, but missing, say, G-Sync, isn&#39;t a killer if you only game on a PS5 or Xbox.</p><h2> The best gaming TVs you can get right now</h2><p> We&#39;re updating this guide during a transitional period for the TV market, as most of the major brands began selling their newest TVs for 2023 relatively recently. That means the new sets&#39; prices are generally <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lgs-2023-oled-tvs-arrive-in-late-march-starting-at-1299-175513466.html">still higher</a> than last year&#39;s models, which manufacturers are selling for less to clear out inventory. Because some of those 2022 TVs are still excellent, they can offer strong value while they&#39;re still available at a discount.</p><p> If you don&#39;t care about paying more for the latest and greatest, most 2023 TVs are technically better than their predecessors, as you&#39;d expect. If you want the most bang for your buck, however, a good set from <em>last year</em> should provide greater value while it&#39;s still in stock. Though Engadget doesn&#39;t formally review TVs, we&#39;re confident in the recommendations below based on our own hands-on experience with some of them and the consensus from TV review sites we trust, such as <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/tv">Rtings</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c813ae39-7d58-41cb-ac66-ad830606ceef&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+New+York+Times&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjODEzYWUzOS03ZDU4LTQxY2ItYWM2Ni1hZDgzMDYwNmNlZWYiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vd2lyZWN1dHRlci9lbGVjdHJvbmljcy90dnMvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmNTg0M2E1MC0xYzExLTQ5ZWUtYmY4Ni0yZmE1ZDQyMTk0NDAifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAe8RPikyUeDiRcg509D2TvK0Zu7BYDM4kvfoWtLMnU3c&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fwirecutter%2Felectronics%2Ftvs%2F&amp;uuid=ImumGWWsbnoDtgSn15790">Wirecutter</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions">Reviewed</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.cnet.com/tech/home-entertainment/">CNET</a> , among others.</p><h2> LG C2 OLED </h2><p><core-commerce id="3211e16838c84158a03229b51d9907a3" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbkAukVTttFuRObF7DhxNl1kKM5n240zhKwHEwumBuz9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09RMLLJPX%2F">LG C2&#39;s</a> OLED panel can&#39;t get as bright as a QD-OLED TV like <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXIUPzmUjz3H9YhxOcw57It92dJRdYPHQzIa3I6Yk94l&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftelevisions-home-theater%2Ftvs%2Foled-tvs%2F65-class-s95b-oled-4k-smart-tv-2022-qn65s95bafxza%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Samsung&#39;s S95B</a> , but it still performs excellently in terms of contrast, input lag, motion response and viewing angles. It&#39;s just less ideal in a brightly-lit room. It follows the HGiG&#39;s HDR guidelines, supports ALLM, works with all the major VRR formats and has four full HDMI 2.1 ports capable of outputting 4K 120Hz with a PS5, Xbox or PC. It also supports all the major HDR standards, including Dolby Vision, and it&#39;s available in a wide variety of sizes, from a <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVo0qVoUBRQnwf8LIAGd-3FVc7ou1QkvSDcYDATAzDKx&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09RMFZZPX%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1%3Fsmid%3DATVPDKIKX0DER%26th%3D1">42-inch model</a> to an <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yah